review_blob: One of the better beers Ive had lately. A nice mixing of both hops and malt, with a faint alcohol bite to it. A bit strong for a seesoin beer, but a taste that gets better with every sip.
I think a very good pale ale. A much more English style ale than an Amearican version. Mild on the hops , but a nice malty pale ale.
A very good ale, not quite extraordinary. A good fresh hop aroma, with a nce hoppy taste to it.
beer_name: Southern Tier PMX (Phin & Matts Extraordinary Ale)

review_blob: One of my favorite wheat beers. Ive heard alot of bad things about it, but in comparing it with others it looks good and tastes edven better. try it if you likr a good hefeweissbier.

I bought this beer just to see if it was ant good for the price. At 4.99 it was a steal. Nice amber color, beautiful off white head. The taste definatley didnt disappoint. A very good APA, at an incredible price. Better than some I have tasted lately that were twice the price.
Im not sure , hoping I just have a bad bottle, but  I didnt like this wheat beer at all. Virtually no head . Very thin with a sweetish taste.
while not the best  example of a British Strong Ale I have to say not a bad beer.
